["Vuka is a river in eastern Croatia, a right tributary of the Danube river. At 112 kilometres (70 miles), it is the 13th-longest river flowing through Croatia and it has a drainage area of 644 square kilometres (249 square miles).[1] The river is located in Vukovar-Srijem County, in the Slavonia region. It empties into the Danube at the town of Vukovar, which got its name from the river.","The ancient name of Pannonian Illyrians for Vuka was Volcos.","This Vukovar-Syrmia County geography article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.","This article related to a river in Croatia is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]